race.comment: KICKER SPLASH (1) bolted in last time, scoring by 4.5 lengths in slick time (16.73) to take a Grade 5 in a new PB this course and distance. In form and can measure up again. WILGUNYA KNIGHT (3) has a strong winning strike-rate over this track and trip with four wins and a placing from six tries. Scored by 5 lengths last time (16.60) in a Grade 5 over 300m at this track. Makes strong appeal on best. CANE TOAD (2) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing second behind Kibet (17.03) in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Expected to be in the finish again. CHARLIE DUTTON (4) is worth consideration after filling a hole in a close finish last time.
